<subSubSection id="48D355CA8F1EFE9048F75669FC63FE55" pageId="336" pageNumber="337" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="007606418F1EFE9048F75669FC63FE55" blockId="336.[151,1437,288,529]" pageId="336" pageNumber="337">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538F1EFE9048F75669FEE4FEAE" bold="true" box="[199,321,325,350]" pageId="336" pageNumber="337">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<emphasis id="32BDDA538F1EFE9049785669FE39FEAD" box="[328,412,325,349]" italics="true" pageId="336" pageNumber="337">Female</emphasis>
: fully winged (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48F1EFE904A7C5669FD78FEAD" box="[588,733,325,349]" captionStart="PLATE 99" captionStartId="337.[151,233,1917,1940]" captionTargetBox="[201,1399,218,1874]" captionTargetId="figure-54@337.[151,1436,193,1896]" captionTargetPageId="337" captionText="PLATE 99. A. Dorsal view. B. Lateral view. C. Chela. A, B. Adryinus sp., Female. Length 6.0 mm (from Olmi 1984). C. Adryinus jini, holotype (from Xu et al. 1995). Scale bar 0.62 mm for C." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278724" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278724/files/figure.png" pageId="336" pageNumber="337">Plate 99A, B</figureCitation>
); palpal formula 6/3; antenna with rhinaria; pronotum crossed by strong transverse furrow (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48F1EFE9049D45645FDF6FE71" box="[484,595,361,385]" captionStart="PLATE 99" captionStartId="337.[151,233,1917,1940]" captionTargetBox="[201,1399,218,1874]" captionTargetId="figure-54@337.[151,1436,193,1896]" captionTargetPageId="337" captionText="PLATE 99. A. Dorsal view. B. Lateral view. C. Chela. A, B. Adryinus sp., Female. Length 6.0 mm (from Olmi 1984). C. Adryinus jini, holotype (from Xu et al. 1995). Scale bar 0.62 mm for C." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278724" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278724/files/figure.png" pageId="336" pageNumber="337">Plate 99B</figureCitation>
); notauli absent; enlarged claw with one subapical tooth and lamellae, or peg-like hairs, or bristles (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48F1EFE90498D56A1FD8EFE55" box="[445,555,397,421]" captionStart="PLATE 99" captionStartId="337.[151,233,1917,1940]" captionTargetBox="[201,1399,218,1874]" captionTargetId="figure-54@337.[151,1436,193,1896]" captionTargetPageId="337" captionText="PLATE 99. A. Dorsal view. B. Lateral view. C. Chela. A, B. Adryinus sp., Female. Length 6.0 mm (from Olmi 1984). C. Adryinus jini, holotype (from Xu et al. 1995). Scale bar 0.62 mm for C." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278724" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278724/files/figure.png" pageId="336" pageNumber="337">Plate 99C</figureCitation>
); tibial spurs 1/0/1. 
<emphasis id="32BDDA538F1EFE904B3D56A1FCE3FE55" box="[781,838,397,421]" italics="true" pageId="336" pageNumber="337">Male</emphasis>
: unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="48D355CA8F1EFE9048F7569CFCC4FE39" box="[199,865,432,457]" pageId="336" pageNumber="337" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="007606418F1EFE9048F7569CFCC4FE39" blockId="336.[151,1437,288,529]" box="[199,865,432,457]" pageId="336" pageNumber="337">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538F1EFE9048F7569CFEC5FE39" bold="true" box="[199,352,432,457]" pageId="336" pageNumber="337">Distribution.</emphasis>
Afrotropical, 
<collectingRegion id="C20DC8A38F1EFE9049CF569DFDFBFE39" box="[511,606,433,457]" country="Democratic Republic of the Congo" name="Orientale" pageId="336" pageNumber="337">Oriental</collectingRegion>
, Nearctic, Neotropical.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="48D355CA8F1EFE9048F756F9FC73FDE1" pageId="336" pageNumber="337" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="007606418F1EFE9048F756F9FE2BFE1D" blockId="336.[151,1437,288,529]" box="[199,398,469,493]" pageId="336" pageNumber="337">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538F1EFE9048F756F9FEB4FE1D" bold="true" box="[199,273,469,493]" pageId="336" pageNumber="337">Hosts.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="007606418F1EFE9048F756D5FC73FDE1" blockId="336.[151,1437,288,529]" box="[199,982,504,529]" pageId="336" pageNumber="337">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538F1EFE9048F756D5FED1FDE1" bold="true" box="[199,372,504,529]" pageId="336" pageNumber="337">World species.</emphasis>
Twelve species are known, one in the 
<collectingRegion id="C20DC8A38F1EFE904B1456D5FC77FDE1" box="[804,978,505,529]" country="Democratic Republic of the Congo" name="Orientale" pageId="336" pageNumber="337">Oriental region</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
